{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017xKFU6cNggSaoXFXxb1BDT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## How typeflow fetches & decrypts per-org API keys for the AI Flow Builder\n\n**Flow** (see `server/services/ai/agent-executor.ts:118-141`, function `getApiKey`):\n\n1. Receives `organizationId` and `credentialId` from the executing node.\n2. Queries the `credentials` table via Drizzle, filtered by **both** `id = credentialId` AND `organizationId = organizationId` — so an org can only ever decrypt its own credentials (`server/services/ai/agent-executor.ts:128-133`).\n3. Throws `Credential not found` if no row matches.\n4. Passes the row's encrypted `config` string into the decryption helper, typed as `{ apiKey: string; baseUrl?: string }`, and returns `{ apiKey, baseUrl }` to the caller (which then constructs the OpenAI/Anthropic SDK client).\n\n**Helper that decrypts the credential payload:**\n\n> **`decryptObject`** — imported from `@/lib/encryption` (`server/services/ai/agent-executor.ts:122`).\n\nUsed as: `decryptObject<{ apiKey: string; baseUrl?: string }>(cred.config as string)` (`agent-executor.ts:139`).\n\nThe same helper is used by the text-classifier path (`server/services/ai/text-classifier-executor.ts:29, 38`), confirming it's the single decryption entry point for stored credential blobs across the AI executors.\n\n---\n\nThis was a research question, not an implementation request — no plan file is needed. Let me know if you'd like me to dig into `lib/encryption.ts` itself (e.g. cipher, key source, IV handling), or trace how `credentialId` gets onto a node in the first place."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18315,"cache_read_input_tokens":19320,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":18315},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"95d2ae66-5ce8-4f8e-94f0-b8af518b4659","uuid":"32abe864-76ea-405b-a7c6-6c3937e6cd61"}
